.TH "pci_find_next_ht_capability" 9 "pci_find_next_ht_capability" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_find_next_ht_capability \- query a device's HyperTransport capabilities
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u8" pci_find_next_ht_capability
.BI "(struct pci_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "u8 pos "  ","
.BI "int ht_cap "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
PCI device to query
.IP "pos" 12
Position from which to continue searching
.IP "ht_cap" 12
HyperTransport capability code
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
To be used in conjunction with \fBpci_find_ht_capability\fP to search for
all capabilities matching \fIht_cap\fP. \fIpos\fP should always be a value returned
from \fBpci_find_ht_capability\fP.

NB. To be 100% safe against broken PCI devices, the caller should take
steps to avoid an infinite loop.
